WEBVTT

00:04.656 --> 00:08.573
PREVIOUSLY ON
"PUSHING DAISIES"...

00:08.617 --> 00:10.488
OHH!

00:10.532 --> 00:11.489
WHO ARE YOU?

00:11.533 --> 00:14.057
YOU WERE MY FIRST KISS.

00:14.101 --> 00:15.711
YOU WERE MY
FIRST KISS, TOO.

00:15.754 --> 00:18.148
YOU TOUCH MURDER VICTIMS,
YOU ASK WHO KILLED THEM.

00:18.192 --> 00:19.932
YOU TOUCH THEM AGAIN,
THEY GO BACK TO BEING DEAD,

00:19.976 --> 00:21.499
AND YOU COLLECT
THE REWARD?

00:21.543 --> 00:22.674
THAT'S IT IN A NUTSHELL.

00:22.718 --> 00:24.024
ARE YOU
THE BUSINESS PARTNER?

00:24.067 --> 00:25.460
YES, MA'AM.

00:25.503 --> 00:27.027
DOESN'T SHE LOOK A LOT
LIKE THAT DEAD GIRL?

00:27.070 --> 00:29.551
SHE LOOKS EXACTLYLIKE
THAT DEAD GIRL.

00:29.594 --> 00:31.770
DO YOU...TOUCH ANYTHING?

00:31.814 --> 00:33.729
I T-TOUCH LOTS OF THINGS.

00:33.772 --> 00:35.600
DOES HE TOUCH YOU?

00:35.644 --> 00:37.559
I'D KISS YOU
IF IT WOULDN'T KILL ME.

00:37.602 --> 00:39.909
Emerson:
ARE YOU IN LOVE WITH HER?
IT'S THAT LEVEL OF STUPID.

00:39.952 --> 00:41.998
I KIND OF KILLED HER DAD
WHEN I WAS 10.

00:42.042 --> 00:43.391
SHE DOESN'T KNOW.

00:43.434 --> 00:45.088
I JUST THOUGHT MY WORLD
WOULD BE A BETTER PLACE

00:45.132 --> 00:46.437
IF YOU WERE IN IT.

00:46.481 --> 00:48.570
IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE
I SHOULD KNOW?

00:48.613 --> 00:49.788
NO.

00:57.013 --> 00:58.754
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

00:58.797 --> 01:01.496
Narrator: AT THIS VERY MOMENT,
IN THE TOWN OF NORTH THRUSH,

01:01.539 --> 01:04.020
YOUNG NED WAS 9 YEARS, 33 WEEKS,

01:04.064 --> 01:07.719
6 DAYS, 20 HOURS,
AND 34 MINUTES OLD.

01:07.763 --> 01:10.157
HE STOOD
ON THE EXACT SPOT WHERE,

01:10.200 --> 01:12.202
4 WEEKS AND 2 DAYS PREVIOUSLY,

01:12.246 --> 01:16.467
HIS FATHER HAD DEPOSITED HIM AT
THE LONGBURROW SCHOOL FOR BOYS.

01:20.602 --> 01:23.257
AS YOUNG NED'S MOTHER
HAD DIED RECENTLY,

01:23.300 --> 01:26.912
THERE WAS REASSURING PHYSICAL
CONTACT AND PARTING WORDS.

01:26.956 --> 01:29.001
"I'LL BE BACK."

01:29.045 --> 01:31.613
HE LIED.

01:31.656 --> 01:34.094
THE SADNESS AND DREAD
WHICH THE BOY FELT

01:34.137 --> 01:38.446
WERE NOT SO MUCH A PRODUCT
OF THE LONGBURROW SCHOOL.

01:38.489 --> 01:40.622
YOUNG NED'S ACUTE DISCOMFORT
CAME FROM THE KNOWLEDGE

01:40.665 --> 01:44.278
THAT WHEN HE TOUCHED A DEAD
THING, IT CAME BACK TO LIFE.

01:44.321 --> 01:46.976
THE OTHER BOYS ASSUMED
HIS INTROVERTED NATURE

01:47.019 --> 01:49.283
WAS A PRODUCT OF WEAKNESS
AND CODDLING.

01:49.326 --> 01:52.155
THINKING OF REVENGE
AND ALSO NOT THINKING AT ALL,

01:52.199 --> 01:55.985
YOUNG NED VOLUNTEERED TO ASSIST
WITH THAT DAY'S SCIENCE PROJECT.

01:58.640 --> 02:01.077
YOUNG NED'S SECRET GIFT
WAS GOVERNED

02:01.121 --> 02:02.905
BY THREE SIMPLE RULES --

02:02.948 --> 02:06.561
TOUCH A DEAD THING ONCE, ALIVE.

02:18.747 --> 02:20.749
[ SCREAMING ]

02:24.709 --> 02:27.669
TOUCH A DEAD THING AGAIN...

02:29.627 --> 02:32.021
...DEAD FOREVER.

02:32.064 --> 02:34.371
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

02:39.724 --> 02:43.206
KEEP A DEAD THING ALIVE
FOR MORE THAN A MINUTE...

02:43.250 --> 02:47.341
AND SOMETHING ELSE HAS TO DIE.

02:47.384 --> 02:50.213
HIS GIFT HAD, ONCE AGAIN,
BROUGHT HIM GREAT DISTRESS

02:50.257 --> 02:51.954
IN PLACE OF GREAT JOY.

02:51.997 --> 02:55.305
HE VOWED TO KEEP THE STRANGE
DETAILS OF HIS STRANGE LIFE

02:55.349 --> 02:57.177
SECRET FROM THE WORLD FOREVER.

02:57.220 --> 02:59.570
ARE YOU RESPONSIBLE
FOR THIS?

02:59.614 --> 03:03.487
Narrator: SO, YOUNG NED DID WHAT
HIS FATHER HAD DONE TO HIM

03:03.531 --> 03:05.663
ONLY 31 DAYS BEFORE.

03:05.707 --> 03:06.534
NO.

03:06.577 --> 03:08.100
Narrator: HE LIED.

03:08.144 --> 03:12.017
FOR THE NEXT 19 YEARS,
29 WEEKS, AND 2 DAYS,

03:12.061 --> 03:14.977
KEEPING SECRETS
WORKED BEAUTIFULLY.

03:22.158 --> 03:24.247
THE BOY BECAME THE PIE MAKER,

03:24.291 --> 03:27.381
AND THE PIE MAKER
DECEIVED WITH EASE...

03:27.424 --> 03:28.817
UNTIL CHUCK.

03:28.860 --> 03:30.471
THIS IS STRANGE.

03:30.514 --> 03:32.473
Narrator: CHARLOTTE CHARLES
HAD BEEN ALIVE

03:32.516 --> 03:37.086
FOR 28 YEARS, 24 WEEKS, 3 DAYS,
11 HOURS, AND 51 MINUTES

03:37.129 --> 03:38.957
BEFORE SHE WAS MURDERED.

03:39.001 --> 03:40.394
IS THIS STRANGE?

03:40.437 --> 03:41.873
THIS IS NOT STRANGE.

03:41.917 --> 03:43.962
UNUSUAL, MAYBE ECCENTRIC,
IN A QUAINT WAY,

03:44.006 --> 03:45.355
LIKE DESSERT SPOONS.

03:45.399 --> 03:46.617
Narrator:
REVIVED BY THE PIE MAKER

03:46.661 --> 03:48.576
AND GIVEN A SECOND CHANCE
AT LIFE,

03:48.619 --> 03:50.099
SHE HAD MANY QUESTIONS.

03:50.142 --> 03:52.754
I HAVE SOMANY QUESTIONS,
MY MIND WANDERS.

03:52.797 --> 03:55.322
YOU NEED TO FEED IT WARM MILK
AND A TURKEY SANDWICH.

03:55.365 --> 03:57.715
LET IT CURL UP IN A SUNNY SPOT
AND TAKE A NAP.

03:57.759 --> 03:59.108
I MISS MY AUNTS.

03:59.151 --> 04:02.329
OF COURSE.
DO YOU MISS THEM A LOT?

04:02.372 --> 04:04.983
A LITTLE.

04:07.290 --> 04:09.771
ALL THE TIME?

04:09.814 --> 04:11.903
NOW AND THEN.

04:11.947 --> 04:15.777
Narrator:
AS CHUCK SPOKE, SHE REALIZED
HER SECRETS WERE "REALLY A LOT"

04:15.820 --> 04:19.476
AND "EVERY MINUTE,"
IN THAT ORDER.

04:19.520 --> 04:21.435
HOW MANY PEOPLE
HAVE YOU TOUCHED?

04:21.478 --> 04:23.306
PEOPLE OR ANIMALS?
CROSSING.

04:23.350 --> 04:25.961
DIGBY DOESN'T COUNT.DIGBY DOESCOUNT.

04:26.004 --> 04:28.006
NO ONE'S BEEN THROUGH
AS MUCH WITH ME AS DIGBY.

04:28.050 --> 04:29.791
HOW MANY PEOPLE HAVE YOU
BROUGHT BACK TO LIFE?

04:29.834 --> 04:31.271
IT'S NOT LIKE I WALK AROUND

04:31.314 --> 04:33.316
REVIVING CHILDHOOD SWEETHEARTS
WILLY-NILLY.

04:33.360 --> 04:35.449
WELL, WHAT ABOUT EMERSON, HUH?
OH, COMING THROUGH!

04:35.492 --> 04:37.277
YOU TOUCHED LOTS OF PEOPLE
WITH EMERSON.

04:37.320 --> 04:39.104
FOR WORK.

04:39.148 --> 04:40.802
JUST BECAUSE YOU KILL THEM
AGAIN AS SOON AS YOU GET
WHAT YOU WANT

04:40.845 --> 04:43.195
DOESN'T MAKE IT
ANY DIFFERENT.
YES, IT DOES.

04:43.239 --> 04:44.936
COMING THROUGH.

04:51.378 --> 04:53.380
AND CAN WE NOT SAY "KILL"?
I TOUCH THEM AGAIN IS ALL,

04:53.423 --> 04:55.469
AND THEY SNAP RIGHT BACK
TO THE WAY THEY'RE
SUPPOSED TO BE.

04:55.512 --> 04:57.209
AM I THE RUBBER BAND
THAT BROKE?

04:57.253 --> 04:58.646
CHUCK, YOU'RE
THE ONLY HUMAN BEING

04:58.689 --> 05:00.256
I'VE EVER MADE
ALIVE AGAIN TO STAY.

05:01.649 --> 05:03.520
Narrator: HE LIED.

05:03.564 --> 05:06.480
IN FACT, THE PIE MAKER HAD KEPT
ONE OTHER PERSON ALIVE

05:06.523 --> 05:08.177
FOR LONGER THAN A MINUTE.

05:08.220 --> 05:11.659
USING THE GIFT TO TEMPORARILY
REVIVE HIS OWN MOTHER,

05:11.702 --> 05:16.925
THE UNINTENDED EFFECT ON CHUCK'S
FATHER HAD BEEN MORE PERMANENT.

05:18.535 --> 05:21.930
THE PIE MAKER OFTEN ASKED
HIMSELF IF HE WOULD EVER BE ABLE

05:21.973 --> 05:23.279
TO TELL CHUCK THIS SECRET.

05:23.323 --> 05:24.411
YOUR EYE'S TWITCHING.

05:24.454 --> 05:25.455
IS IT?

05:29.633 --> 05:32.332
THIS IS SUCH A SMALL
CHEESE BOX.

05:32.375 --> 05:35.465
Narrator:
THE AUNTS WHO HAD RAISED CHUCK
HAD TAUGHT HER TO BELIEVE

05:35.509 --> 05:37.902
THAT THE LARGE WHITE APPLIANCE
IN THE KITCHEN

05:37.946 --> 05:39.687
HAD A FAIRLY NARROW PURPOSE.

05:39.730 --> 05:41.819
AUNT LILY, IS IT OKAY TO FREEZE
THE CAMEMBERT?

05:41.863 --> 05:43.995
I'D RATHER NOT WEDGE IT BETWEEN
THE EDAM AND THE PANEER!

05:44.039 --> 05:45.867
OR I COULD AIR OUT
THE GOUDA!

05:45.910 --> 05:48.783
Narrator: IN FACT, YOUNG CHUCK
DID NOT REFER TO A REFRIGERATOR

05:48.826 --> 05:52.743
AS ANYTHING BUT A CHEESE BOX
UNTIL SHE WAS 17.

05:54.484 --> 05:59.402
AS CHUCK CONSIDERED THE LIFE
SHE COULD NEVER GO BACK TO,

05:59.446 --> 06:02.710
OLIVE SNOOK CONSIDERED
THE CHANGES IN HER OWN LIFE --

06:02.753 --> 06:05.582
FOREMOST, THE MYSTERIOUS
BRUNETTE ENCROACHING

06:05.626 --> 06:08.280
ON THE MAN SHE HERSELF LOVED.

06:08.324 --> 06:11.414
FROM HER PERCH, THE JEALOUS
YET AGILE NEIGHBOR

06:11.458 --> 06:14.548
WAS ABLE TO CONFIRM ONLY ONE
PLEASING DETAIL.

06:14.591 --> 06:17.551
THERE'S A SURPRISING LACK
OF PHYSICAL CONTACT.

06:17.594 --> 06:19.161
OH, CRAP.

06:19.204 --> 06:20.554
[ THUD, MIRROR SHATTERS ]

06:20.597 --> 06:21.903
Narrator:
ONE MILE TO THE WEST,

06:21.946 --> 06:24.296
EMERSON COD WAS ALSO
NOT THRILLED.

06:24.340 --> 06:27.169
DURING TIMES OF STRESS
OR ANXIETY, HE LIKED TO KNIT.

06:27.212 --> 06:29.911
SINCE THE ARRIVAL OF
THE DEAD GIRL WHO WAS NOT DEAD,

06:29.954 --> 06:34.132
HE FOUND THE STOCKINETTE STITCH
TO BE ESPECIALLY RELAXING.

06:34.176 --> 06:36.134
EMERSON COD.

06:36.178 --> 06:39.355
Narrator:
BUT NO STITCH WAS A SUBSTITUTE
FOR A GOOD MURDER CASE.

06:39.399 --> 06:40.878
THANKS. GOT IT.

06:45.840 --> 06:48.451
MEET ME AT THE MORGUE
IN 15 MINUTES.

06:48.495 --> 06:52.760
Narrator:
AS HE FINISHED PEARLING THE ROW,
HE WISHED ALOUD...

06:52.803 --> 06:54.892
SHE BETTER NOT COME.

06:59.114 --> 07:00.985
HI, EMERSON.

07:02.987 --> 07:05.076
ISN'T THIS EXCITING?

07:05.120 --> 07:07.427
[ GRUNTS ]

07:08.689 --> 07:09.646
UH...

07:09.690 --> 07:10.691
HEY!

07:11.953 --> 07:13.302
WHAT'S SHEDOING HERE?

07:13.345 --> 07:14.477
SAID SHE DIDN'T CLIMB OUT
OF A COFFIN

07:14.521 --> 07:15.609
FOR ME TO KEEP HER
IN A BOX.

07:15.652 --> 07:16.566
SHE THE BOSS OF YOU?

07:16.610 --> 07:17.828
I'M THE BOSS OF ME.

07:17.872 --> 07:19.090
DEAD GIRL'S GOT TO GO.

07:19.134 --> 07:20.265
DEAD GIRL'S
NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

07:20.309 --> 07:21.571
YOU DON'T KNOW NOTHING
ABOUT HER

07:21.615 --> 07:22.877
EXCEPT SHE HAD SOFT LIPS
WHEN SHE WAS 10.

07:22.920 --> 07:23.878
THAT SHOULD BE ENOUGH.

07:23.921 --> 07:25.270
WELL, I DON'T LIKE IT.

07:33.017 --> 07:34.192
[ KNOCKING ]HEY!

07:35.759 --> 07:37.239
WHAT DID YOU GUYS
TALK ABOUT?

07:37.282 --> 07:39.676
I'D REALLY LIKE TO GET OUT
OF THIS CAR SOON.

07:39.720 --> 07:42.113
IS HE UPSET YOU BROUGHT
YOUR CHILDHOOD SWEETHEART
BACK TO LIFE?

07:42.157 --> 07:43.637
HE BARELY KNOWS YOU'RE HERE.

07:46.030 --> 07:49.730
Narrator:
IN FACT, EMERSON COD HAD
FINISHED KNITTING A SWEATER VEST

07:49.773 --> 07:53.995
AND TWO HANDGUN COZIES IN
THE WEEK SINCE CHUCK'S RETURN.

07:54.038 --> 07:55.997
SWEET.

07:56.040 --> 07:57.912
DO I REALLY HAVE TO SIT
IN BACK FROM NOW ON?

07:57.955 --> 07:59.261
IT'S FOR YOUR OWN SAFETY.

07:59.304 --> 08:00.654
YOU SOUND LIKE MY DAD.

08:00.697 --> 08:03.178
IF MY HAND BRUSHES YOURS,
YOU'D BE DEAD.

08:03.221 --> 08:05.833
HE DIDN'T SAY THAT.

08:05.876 --> 08:08.575
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:08.618 --> 08:11.534
SO IT'S PROBABLY BETTER
IF YOU STAY IN THE CAR
FOR THESE MORGUE VISITS.

08:11.578 --> 08:12.709
SOMEONE MIGHT
RECOGNIZE YOU.

08:12.753 --> 08:15.407
YOU REALLY CAN'T COME IN.

08:15.451 --> 08:16.757
DID I SAY "CAN"?

08:16.800 --> 08:18.672
BECAUSE I SWALLOW
MY CONSONANTS SOMETIMES.

08:18.715 --> 08:20.369
"N'T. N'T."

08:20.412 --> 08:21.675
CAN'TCOME IN.

08:21.718 --> 08:23.372
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
GOT THAT HIT-AND-RUN?

08:23.415 --> 08:25.853
WE'RE FROM THE GOVERNMENT
SAFETY PLACE?

08:25.896 --> 08:27.332
[ With teeth clenched ]
IS THAT A QUESTION?

08:27.376 --> 08:29.160
GOVERNMENT SAFETY PLACE.

08:29.204 --> 08:31.859
MM-HMM.

08:31.902 --> 08:33.382
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE.

08:33.425 --> 08:34.862
ONE BERNARD SLAYBECK,

08:34.905 --> 08:37.299
AN UNMARRIED AUTOMOTIVE SAFETY
SPECIALIST --

08:37.342 --> 08:40.824
35 YEARS, 10 WEEKS, 7 HOURS,
AND 3 MINUTES OLD --

08:40.868 --> 08:43.653
WAS FOUND DEAD
BY THE SIDE OF THE ROAD...

08:43.697 --> 08:45.394
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

08:48.528 --> 08:51.400
...THE APPARENT VICTIM
OF A HIT-AND-RUN DRIVER.

08:51.443 --> 08:53.445
[ CAR ENGINE ROARS, THUD ]

08:53.489 --> 08:56.971
Narrator:
AS THERE WERE NO WITNESSES,
THE POLICE ARE OFFERING A REWARD

08:57.014 --> 08:59.364
FOR INFORMATION LEADING TO
THE ARREST OF THE KILLER.

08:59.408 --> 09:00.583
I'M GONNA WAIT BACK HERE.

09:00.627 --> 09:02.237
YOU DON'T LIKE DEAD BODIES,
DO YOU?

09:02.280 --> 09:04.065
NOT WHEN THEY SIT UP
AND TALK.

09:04.108 --> 09:05.588
POOR MAN.
JUST TOUCH IT.

09:05.632 --> 09:07.198
I'M STARTING THE WATCH.

09:07.242 --> 09:09.287
[ WATCH TICKING ]

09:09.331 --> 09:11.202
HEY.
HEY.

09:11.246 --> 09:13.074
WHY IS EVERYTHING
SO BLURRY?

09:13.117 --> 09:15.598
PROBABLY BECAUSE YOUR EYEBALLS
ARE FLAT.ASK THE QUESTION.

09:15.642 --> 09:17.774
MR. SLAYBECK, DO YOU --DO YOU HAVE
ANY LAST REQUESTS,

09:17.818 --> 09:19.950
UNFINISHED BUSINESS FROM THIS
LIFE WE CAN HELP YOU WITH?

09:19.994 --> 09:21.561
DON'T LET HER DO THIS.IS THIS HEAVEN?

09:21.604 --> 09:23.737
COULD BE.
NO, IT'S NOT.

09:23.780 --> 09:25.347
IS THAT GOD?
NO, IT'S NOT.

09:25.390 --> 09:27.088
I'M CONFUSED,
BECAUSE I'M A BUDDHIST.

09:27.131 --> 09:28.611
BUDDHISM IS FASCINATING,
ISN'T IT?

09:28.655 --> 09:30.308
DID IT HELP YOU
IN YOUR FINAL MOMENTS?

09:30.352 --> 09:32.093
SHE'S WASTING MY MINUTE.

09:32.136 --> 09:33.877
WHAT'S WITH THIS MINUTE? AND
WHEN DID IT BECOME YOURMINUTE?

09:33.921 --> 09:35.313
SURE THE HELL AIN'T YOURS.

09:35.357 --> 09:37.925
HEY, IT'S EVERYONE'S MINUTE,
OR, UH, 22 SECONDS.

09:37.968 --> 09:39.622
CAN YOU GET A MESSAGE TO EARTH?

09:39.666 --> 09:41.581
CAN YOU TELL JEANINE
IN PROMOTIONS THAT I LOVED HER?

09:41.624 --> 09:43.191
OF COURSE.

09:43.234 --> 09:44.932
MR. SLAYBECK, IF YOU COULD
REMEMBER ANYTHING ABOUT

09:44.975 --> 09:46.237
WHOEVER WAS DRIVING
THE HIT-AND-RUN VEHICLE
THAT KILLED YOU,

09:46.281 --> 09:47.978
I THINK WE CAN GET YOU
SOME JUSTICE.

09:48.022 --> 09:50.241
WHAT HIT-AND-RUN? I WAS KILLED
BY A CRASH-TEST DUMMY.

10:05.126 --> 10:07.824
I'M NOT GOD, BUT IF I WAS,
I'D BE AN ANGRY GOD.

10:07.868 --> 10:09.696
OH, WE GAVE IT
OUR BEST SHOT.

10:09.739 --> 10:12.089
SO, A CRASH-TEST DUMMY
KILLED BERNARD.

10:12.133 --> 10:13.569
BERNARD WAS DELUSIONAL.

10:13.613 --> 10:15.310
IT'S STILL A CLUE.IT'S A DEAD END.

10:15.353 --> 10:17.660
AND NOT THE KIND OF DEAD END
YOU CAN UNDEAD

10:17.704 --> 10:20.184
AND THEN REDEAD AGAIN,
LIKE YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO.

10:20.228 --> 10:21.490
IT'S MY FAULT?

10:21.533 --> 10:23.405
WHEN YOU GET ALL JABBERWOCKY
IN MY MINUTE,

10:23.448 --> 10:25.450
IT'S HARD TO FOLLOW UP
ON "THE DUMMY DID IT."

10:25.494 --> 10:27.148
GOT TO GET
SOME REAL LEADS NOW.

10:27.191 --> 10:28.540
ISN'T THAT WHAT A P.I.'s
SUPPOSED TO DO?

10:28.584 --> 10:30.368
INVESTIGATE?
ISN'T THAT THE FUN PART?

10:30.412 --> 10:32.632
THE FUN PART'S
COUNTING MY MONEY
IN THE BUBBLE BATH.

10:35.765 --> 10:37.637
NICE IMAGE.

10:41.205 --> 10:43.033
OH, BOY.

10:43.077 --> 10:44.905
WHAT'S THE POOP?

10:44.948 --> 10:45.949
"THE POOP"?

10:45.993 --> 10:47.081
THE POOP.

10:47.124 --> 10:48.691
SCOOP, SKINNY, THE HAPS,

10:48.735 --> 10:51.215
THE DILLYO, THE 411 --
P.I. LINGO.

10:51.259 --> 10:52.260
RHUBARB.

10:52.303 --> 10:53.870
WHAT'S THAT MEAN?

10:53.914 --> 10:56.525
P.I. SECRET CODE FOR "GET ME
A DAMN SLICE OF RHUBARB."

10:56.568 --> 10:58.614
THIS ISN'T PIES 'R' US,
PIE CITY,

10:58.658 --> 11:00.747
OR THOUSANDS OF PIES
IN ONE PLACE.

11:00.790 --> 11:04.925
THIS IS A BELLS-ON-THE-DOOR,
PIES-BAKING, MOM-AND-POP PLACE.

11:04.968 --> 11:06.883
WE CHITCHAT HERE.

11:09.799 --> 11:11.366
CHIT!

11:13.020 --> 11:14.412
CHAT.

11:14.456 --> 11:15.631
YOU GOT IT.

11:15.675 --> 11:18.721
SO, WHO'S THE FUNNY GIRL
STUCK TO NED?

11:18.765 --> 11:19.940
CHILDHOOD SWEETHEART.

11:19.983 --> 11:23.030
STILL SWEET -- HIS HEART?

11:23.073 --> 11:25.119
YOU WANT THE TRUTH?

11:25.162 --> 11:27.556
Narrator: OLIVE SNOOK
DID NOT WANT THE TRUTH,

11:27.599 --> 11:29.689
BUT HER HEART WAS SO FULL

11:29.732 --> 11:32.300
THAT IT REACHED UP
AND NODDED HER HEAD.

11:32.343 --> 11:35.172
HE DIGS HER IN A WAY
HE DEFINITELY DOESN'T DIG YOU.

11:42.005 --> 11:45.443
I-I'LL JUST GO GET
YOUR PIE.

11:45.487 --> 11:47.358
DO THEY TOUCH MUCH?

11:47.402 --> 11:48.708
WISH THEY WOULD.

11:51.449 --> 11:53.016
EMERSON THINKS I'M USELESS.

11:53.060 --> 11:55.671
YOU'RE NOT USELESS.
HERE, LET ME. YOU SIFT.

11:55.715 --> 11:58.630
USELESS IS AN EMPTY SOAP
DISPENSER IN A RESTROOM,

11:58.674 --> 12:00.937
STANDING AROUND REMINDING PEOPLE
WHAT YOU COULD BE DOING,

12:00.981 --> 12:02.504
BUT DOING NOTHING AT ALL.

12:02.547 --> 12:03.810
UH, MORE FLOUR.

12:03.853 --> 12:05.376
I CAN'T BE ALIVE AGAIN
FOR NO REASON.

12:05.420 --> 12:08.292
I SUPPOSE I COULD BE,
BUT WHERE'S THE FUN IN THAT?

12:08.336 --> 12:10.033
WE'LL FIND THE KILLER.
EMERSON'S GOOD AT WHAT HE DOES.

12:10.077 --> 12:11.774
ALL EMERSON CARES ABOUT
IS THE REWARD.

12:11.818 --> 12:13.471
MAYBE THAT'S ENOUGH.IT'S NOTENOUGH.

12:13.515 --> 12:15.430
ENOUGH FLOUR.
OH.

12:15.473 --> 12:16.866
WELL, WHAT ABOUT JEANINE?

12:16.910 --> 12:18.389
SHE NEEDS TO KNOW
THAT BERNARD LOVED HER.

12:18.433 --> 12:19.826
IT WAS HIS DYING WISH.

12:19.869 --> 12:21.088
IT'S SO SAD.

12:21.131 --> 12:22.393
WELL,
WE'LL CUSHION THE BLOW.

12:22.437 --> 12:23.960
NOT A BIG FAN OF THE BLOW.WE'LL BRING PIE.

12:24.004 --> 12:27.572
SOMEONE DIES, YOU BRING FOOD.
IT'S WHAT YOU DO.

12:27.616 --> 12:29.661
Narrator: AS THE PIE MAKER
SECRETLY THOUGHT

12:29.705 --> 12:31.751
HOW MUCH BETTER
HIS LIFE HAD BECOME

12:31.794 --> 12:33.883
SINCE CHUCK HAD RETURNED...

12:41.064 --> 12:43.371
...OLIVE SECRETLY FELT
THE DISTANCE

12:43.414 --> 12:46.766
BETWEEN HER AND THE PIE MAKER
GROW MORE AND MORE VAST

12:46.809 --> 12:49.159
UNTIL IT SEEMED
SHE MIGHT AS WELL BE

12:49.203 --> 12:51.553
ON THE OTHER SIDE
OF THE UNIVERSE.

12:55.078 --> 12:57.037
Woman:
THE EARTH IS OUR ONLY HOME.

12:57.080 --> 12:59.256
IF WE DON'T TAKE CARE OF IT,
WHO WILL?

12:59.300 --> 13:01.302
IMAGINE A VEHICLE
SO REVOLUTIONARY,

13:01.345 --> 13:03.391
IT RUNS ON AN EXTRAORDINARY
NEW FUEL

13:03.434 --> 13:06.176
DERIVED FROM A RENEWABLE PLANT
FOUND EVERYWHERE --

13:06.220 --> 13:07.830
THE DANDELION.

13:07.874 --> 13:10.702
INTRODUCING THE DANDY LION SX.

13:10.746 --> 13:12.487
IT'LL BLOW YOU AWAY.

13:12.530 --> 13:15.577
Narrator: WHILE SOME CAME
TO DANDY LION INDUSTRIES

13:15.620 --> 13:17.405
TO SEE THE CAR OF THE FUTURE,

13:17.448 --> 13:20.756
CHUCK AND THE PIE MAKER CAME
WITH A WISH FROM THE PAST.

13:20.800 --> 13:23.324
A CAR THAT RUNS ON DANDELIONS?
THAT'S SO NEAT!

13:23.367 --> 13:25.195
HOW ARE WE GONNA
FIND JEANINE?

13:25.239 --> 13:26.240
THIS WAY, PEOPLE.

13:26.283 --> 13:27.241
OVER HERE.

13:27.284 --> 13:29.373
[ SPEAKING JAPANESE ]

13:44.649 --> 13:46.608
[ SPEAKING JAPANESE ]

14:02.667 --> 14:04.408
...JEANINE FROM PROMOTIONS?

14:04.452 --> 14:05.932
IT'S A PERSONAL MATTER.

14:05.975 --> 14:07.585
THE FLOWER ON THE TURNTABLE.

14:07.629 --> 14:08.935
THANKS.

14:08.978 --> 14:11.241
HAVE A NICE DAY.

14:11.285 --> 14:13.809
PLEASE, DON'T TOUCH!
NO SMUDGES!

14:16.116 --> 14:18.814
NOW, WHO WANTS TO SEE
ALL THE COLORS AVAILABLE

14:18.858 --> 14:20.685
FOR THE DANDY LION SX?

14:23.819 --> 14:25.821
YOU SPEAK JAPANESE? HAI.

14:25.865 --> 14:27.736
WHEN YOU TAKE CARE OF SHUT-INS
YOUR WHOLE LIFE,

14:27.779 --> 14:29.303
YOU HAVE PLENTY OF TIME
TO READ.

14:29.346 --> 14:32.654
DON'T YOU HAVE ANY HIDDEN
TALENTS OR HOBBIES?

14:32.697 --> 14:35.222
I MEAN REGULAR ONES.

14:35.265 --> 14:37.920
Narrator: CHUCK'S LOVE
OF LANGUAGE HAD BEGUN

14:37.964 --> 14:40.923
UPON THE DISCOVERY OF A PORTABLE
CASSETTE-TAPE PLAYER

14:40.967 --> 14:43.447
AND SEVERAL BOXES
OF LANGUAGE COURSES.

14:43.491 --> 14:45.536
[ WOMAN SPEAKING FRENCH]

14:45.580 --> 14:47.451
[ REPEATING IN FRENCH ]

14:47.495 --> 14:49.671
[ WOMAN SPEAKING GERMAN]

14:49.714 --> 14:51.803
[ REPEATING IN GERMAN ]

14:51.847 --> 14:53.805
[ WOMAN SPEAKING SWEDISH]

14:53.849 --> 14:55.807
[ REPEATING IN SWEDISH ]

14:55.851 --> 14:57.766
[ WOMAN SPEAKING CHINESE]

14:57.809 --> 14:59.594
[ REPEATING IN CHINESE ]

14:59.637 --> 15:01.857
[ REPEATING IN CHINESE ]

15:01.901 --> 15:04.686
HI!
FLEX YOUR FLOWER POWER!

15:04.729 --> 15:07.036
WOULD YOU LIKE A FACTSHEET
ON THE DANDY LION SX,

15:07.080 --> 15:08.690
THE "SPORES" CAR OF TOMORROW?

15:08.733 --> 15:11.084
GET IT? "SPORES" CAR?
WELL, I THINK IT'S CUTE.

15:11.127 --> 15:12.955
ARE YOU JEANINE?

15:12.999 --> 15:14.435
AM I IN TROUBLE
FOR MAKING UP SLOGANS?

15:14.478 --> 15:16.045
'CAUSE I'LL SAY
THE "BLOW YOU AWAY" THING,

15:16.089 --> 15:17.525
BUT IT SEEMED KIND OF REDUNDANT

15:17.568 --> 15:19.135
WITH THE COMMERCIAL PLAYING
ALL THE TIME.

15:19.179 --> 15:21.616
WE'RE HERE ON A MORE TRAGIC
MATTER ABOUT BERNARD SLAYBECK.

15:21.659 --> 15:23.574
MAYBE YOU GOT
THE WRONG FLOWER,

15:23.618 --> 15:24.967
BUT I DIDN'T KNOW
ANY BERNARD.

15:25.011 --> 15:25.968
Narrator: SHE LIED.

15:26.012 --> 15:27.230
ARE YOU SURE?

15:27.274 --> 15:29.102
I KNOW WHAT I KNOW.
IS THAT PIE?

15:29.145 --> 15:31.191
IT WAS BAKED SPECIFICALLY
FOR THE RECIPIENT
OF BERNARD'S MESSAGE.

15:31.234 --> 15:34.542
WELL, IT'S A SHAME TO WASTE
A PERFECTLY GOOD PIE.

15:34.585 --> 15:36.761
MAN, THAT SMELLS GOOD.

15:39.721 --> 15:41.027
YOU'RE DROOLING.BERNARD SAID --

15:41.070 --> 15:42.158
HE'S DEAD, RIGHT?

15:42.202 --> 15:43.464
Narrator:
THE FLOWER HAD A SECRET.

15:43.507 --> 15:45.945
YEAH, HE'S DEAD.
ENJOY YOUR PIE.

15:45.988 --> 15:47.990
Narrator: BUT HER TRAINING
AS A DISPLAY MODEL

15:48.034 --> 15:49.992
ALLOWED HER TO CONCEAL
ANY TRACE.

15:50.036 --> 15:51.994
Mark: TIME TO MOVE ON
TO THE NEXT STOP, PEOPLE --

15:52.038 --> 15:54.214
THE CRASH-TEST FACILITY!

15:56.564 --> 15:57.826
"CRASH-TEST FACILITY"?

15:57.869 --> 16:00.002
DUMMIES.
FEEL LIKE TAKING A TOUR?

16:00.046 --> 16:01.699
UH-HUH.

16:01.743 --> 16:04.920
Narrator: SAFELY OUT OF SIGHT,
THE FLOWER BEGAN TO WEEP.

16:04.964 --> 16:08.010
LIKE THE RICH, SUGARY DESSERT
SHE BINGED ON,

16:08.054 --> 16:09.925
HER TEARS WOULD REMAIN WITH HER

16:09.969 --> 16:11.796
FOR ONLY THE NEXT
10 TO 15 MINUTES

16:11.840 --> 16:14.190
BEFORE THEY WOULD BE PURGED
FROM HER BODY,

16:14.234 --> 16:17.759
LIKE THEY HAD NEVER EXISTED.

16:17.802 --> 16:19.456
Mark:
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

16:19.500 --> 16:22.590
WELCOME TO THE DANDY LION
WORLDWIDE CRASH-TEST FACILITY.

16:22.633 --> 16:23.895
[ BEEPS ]

16:32.295 --> 16:33.905
SCIENCE GUYS,

16:33.949 --> 16:35.777
I'D LIKE YOU TO MEET OUR NEWEST
DANDY LION DEALERS

16:35.820 --> 16:38.519
FROM A LITTLE TERRITORY
I LIKE TO CALL ASIA.

16:38.562 --> 16:40.086
[ SPEAKING JAPANESE ]

16:40.129 --> 16:42.262
BANZAI!BANZAI!BANZAI!BANZAI!

16:42.305 --> 16:44.003
SCIENCE GUY, TELL THEM
WHAT HAPPENS IN HERE.

16:44.046 --> 16:46.396
[ Indian accent ]
UM, THIS IS WHERE WE USE

16:46.440 --> 16:48.746
ELECTRONIC
ANTHROPOMORPHIC UNITS...

16:48.790 --> 16:50.574
DUMMY DES.

16:50.618 --> 16:53.969
...TO TEST THE DANDY LION SX
FOR STRUCTURAL INTEGRITY,

16:54.013 --> 16:57.059
AS WELL AS THE VIABILITY
OF ALL THE RESTRAINT-

16:57.103 --> 16:59.279
AND IMPACT-INITIATED
SAFETY SYSTEMS.

16:59.322 --> 17:02.238
WE CRASH THINGS IN HERE.
BOOM DES KA!

17:02.282 --> 17:05.111
[ CHEERING ]

17:05.154 --> 17:08.853
NOW, WHO WANTS
TO PULL THE LEVER?

17:09.724 --> 17:13.380
MNH-MNH-MNH-MNH.

17:28.351 --> 17:30.005
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

17:30.049 --> 17:32.486
Narrator: AS THE GROUP
THRILLED TO THE SIGHT

17:32.529 --> 17:36.142
OF TWISTED METAL AND SIMULATED
LOSS OF LIFE AND LIMB,

17:36.185 --> 17:39.928
CHUCK CAME UPON AN EQUALLY
CHILLING SIGHT OF HER OWN.

17:53.811 --> 17:55.857
ONE OF THESE DUMMIES
IS NOT LIKE THE OTHERS.

17:55.900 --> 17:58.599
WHERE DID HIS CLOTHES GO?

17:58.642 --> 18:00.383
WHERE DID HIS FACE GO?

18:00.427 --> 18:02.994
MAYBE BERNARD WASN'T CRAZY.

18:09.349 --> 18:11.307
THE DUMMY DID IT.

18:11.351 --> 18:13.527
OR AT LEAST SOMEONE
IN A DUMMY MASK AND
AN ORANGE JUMPSUIT.

18:13.570 --> 18:14.571
CHUCK FOUND THE CLUE.

18:14.615 --> 18:15.616
I FOUND THE CLUE.

18:15.659 --> 18:17.183
"CLUE" IS A BOARD GAME.

18:17.226 --> 18:19.663
THE PROFESSOR DID IT IN
THE PARLOR WITH A RUBBER MALLET.

18:19.707 --> 18:22.101
THAT'S A CLUE.
WE FIND EVIDENCE.

18:22.144 --> 18:23.885
YOU GOT TO ADMIT,
THIS MEANS SOMETHING.

18:23.928 --> 18:25.713
IT COULD BE A LEAD.
WHO WOULD HAVE ACCESS?

18:25.756 --> 18:27.845
LOOPY DANDY LION MODELS,
ANGRY TECHNICIANS --

18:27.889 --> 18:29.108
COULD BE ANYBODY.

18:29.151 --> 18:30.718
I DID SOME CHECKING
ON THAT CAR COMPANY.

18:30.761 --> 18:32.459
THEY GOT A LOT RIDING
ON THIS DANDY LION.

18:32.502 --> 18:33.895
LOT OF ANGRY
COMPETITORS, TOO.

18:33.938 --> 18:35.462
WE GOT TO GET BACK
IN THERE TONIGHT.

18:35.505 --> 18:36.985
OH, THAT'S NOT
HOW WE DO IT.

18:37.028 --> 18:38.682
WE GOTTO GET BACK
IN THERE TONIGHT,

18:38.726 --> 18:40.902
SEE IF WHOEVER TOOK THAT
DUMMY MASK LEFT ANY EVIDENCE.

18:40.945 --> 18:42.295
[ SIGHS ]

18:42.338 --> 18:43.383
OLIVE?

18:43.426 --> 18:44.993
HIYA!

18:45.036 --> 18:46.212
WE'RE GOING OUT LATE TONIGHT,
A PRIVILEGE THING,

18:46.255 --> 18:47.909
HARDLY WORTH EXPLAINING.

18:47.952 --> 18:50.564
CAN YOU CLOSE UP?I THINK I JUST DID.

18:50.607 --> 18:52.087
WHAT?

18:52.131 --> 18:53.393
SEE YOU IN THE MORNING.

18:54.698 --> 18:55.960
BYE, OLIVE.

18:56.004 --> 18:57.353
BYE, DIGBY.

18:59.616 --> 19:03.229
Narrator:
OLIVE OFTEN IMAGINED THERE WAS
AN ORCHESTRA IN HER HEART,

19:03.272 --> 19:05.405
MUSIC HEARD ONLY BY HER,

19:05.448 --> 19:07.450
EXCEPT WHEN HER HEART BROKE OPEN

19:07.494 --> 19:10.279
AND IT SPILLED OUT
INTO THE WORLD.

19:11.889 --> 19:18.940
♪ GUESS MINE IS NOT
THE FIRST HEART BROKEN ♪

19:18.983 --> 19:26.077
♪ MY EYES ARE NOT THE FIRST
TO CRY ♪

19:26.121 --> 19:29.124
♪ I'M NOT THE FIRST TO KNOW

19:29.168 --> 19:35.130
♪ THERE'S JUST NO
GETTIN' OVER YOU ♪

19:35.174 --> 19:39.874
♪ I'M HOPELESSLY DEVOTED TO --

19:39.917 --> 19:40.918
EXCUSE ME.

19:43.007 --> 19:44.661
WE'RE CLOSED.

19:49.188 --> 19:55.629
♪ YOU KNOW, I'M JUST A FOOL
WHO'S WILLING ♪

19:55.672 --> 20:01.983
♪ TO SIT AROUND
AND WAIT FOR YOU ♪

20:02.026 --> 20:06.117
♪ BUT, BABY, CAN'T YOU SEE

20:06.161 --> 20:11.819
♪ THERE'S NOTHING LEFT
FOR ME TO DO? ♪

20:11.862 --> 20:16.693
♪ I'M HOPELESSLY DEVOTED --

20:16.737 --> 20:17.825
HI, OLIVE!

20:17.868 --> 20:18.826
HI, MANUEL.

20:18.869 --> 20:20.828
CAN I DO THE FLOORS?

20:20.871 --> 20:22.482
YEAH, OKAY.

20:22.525 --> 20:28.879
♪ BUT NOW THERE'S NOWHERE
TO HIDE ♪

20:28.923 --> 20:32.100
♪ SINCE YOU PUSHED
MY LOVE ASIDE ♪

20:32.143 --> 20:35.886
♪ I'M OUT OF MY HEAD

20:35.930 --> 20:42.328
♪ HOPELESSLY DEVOTED TO YOU

20:42.371 --> 20:47.724
♪ HOPELESSLY DEVOTED TO YOU

20:47.768 --> 20:48.725
[ HOWLING ]

20:48.769 --> 20:51.554
♪ OOOOH

20:51.598 --> 20:53.034
DID YOU SAY SOMETHING?
NO.

20:53.077 --> 20:54.470
[ WHIMPERS ]

21:01.738 --> 21:13.402
♪ HOPELESSLY DEVOTED
TO YOU-U-U-U-U ♪

21:18.189 --> 21:21.192
Narrator: WHILE OLIVE CONSIDERED
HOW MUCH SHE LOVED DIGBY

21:21.236 --> 21:24.500
FOR PAYING ATTENTION TO HER
WHEN THE PIE MAKER WOULD NOT,

21:24.544 --> 21:28.156
AND DIGBY CONSIDERED
HOW MUCH HE LIKED SALT...

21:31.290 --> 21:34.554
...THE PIE MAKER CONSIDERED
WHAT THE SENTENCE WOULD BE

21:34.597 --> 21:37.861
FOR BREAKING AND ENTERING
WITH NO PRIOR CONVICTIONS.

21:52.441 --> 21:54.443
WHERE'D YOU GET THAT?

21:54.487 --> 21:56.271
CONTACTED THE COMPANY
THAT MAKES THESE DOORS

21:56.315 --> 21:57.533
UNDER FALSE PRETENSES.

21:57.577 --> 21:59.100
THEY GAVE ME
A SAMPLE I.D. BADGE,

21:59.143 --> 22:00.797
WHICH I DIGITALLY ALTERED
USING THE MAGNETIC CODE

22:00.841 --> 22:02.669
THAT MATCHES THE SERIAL NUMBER
OF THIS MACHINE.

22:02.712 --> 22:03.670
IS THAT CHEATING?

22:03.713 --> 22:05.672
I DON'T KNOW.
IS THIS?

22:05.715 --> 22:07.369
I GAVE THE SECURITY GUARD
A HUG GOODBYE.

22:07.413 --> 22:09.023
MY UPPER BODY
DISTRACTED HIM

22:09.066 --> 22:11.634
WHILE THESE THINGS I CALL HANDS
TOOK THIS OFF HIS BELT.

22:14.158 --> 22:15.464
[ BEEPS ]

22:19.990 --> 22:21.731
Narrator:
AT THAT MOMENT,

22:21.775 --> 22:25.605
THE PIE MAKER FELT A MIXTURE
OF HAPPINESS AND TREPIDATION.

22:25.648 --> 22:27.694
WHY IS IT ALWAYS A MIXTURE?

22:31.437 --> 22:32.655
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT EMERSON

22:32.699 --> 22:34.135
BESIDES HE PRIVATELY
INVESTIGATES?

22:34.178 --> 22:35.571
WHAT IS SO GREAT
ABOUT KNOWING?

22:35.615 --> 22:37.443
WHEN YOU LIFT UP A ROCK,
DO YOU FIND WHIPPED CREAM?

22:37.486 --> 22:38.444
NO, YOU FIND WORMS.

22:38.487 --> 22:40.620
I SAY NO TO KNOWING.

22:40.663 --> 22:42.143
WE HAVEN'T SEEN EACH OTHER
IN 20 YEARS.

22:42.186 --> 22:43.449
DON'T YOU WANT TO KNOW
ABOUT ME?

22:43.492 --> 22:44.972
I WANT TO KNOW EVERYTHING
ABOUT YOU.

22:45.015 --> 22:47.583
LOOK, WE'VE ALL DONE THINGS
WE'RE NOT PROUD OF.

22:47.627 --> 22:48.845
WE ALL HAVE SECRETS.

22:48.889 --> 22:50.238
WHAT SECRETS?

22:50.281 --> 22:51.587
SKELETONS IN THE CLOSET.

22:51.631 --> 22:53.981
EXACTLY. HOW LONG
HAVE YOU BEEN LISTENING?

22:54.024 --> 22:58.333
THERE ARE SKELETONS
IN THE CLOSET.

23:03.947 --> 23:05.906
THOSE AREN'T SKELETONS.

23:05.949 --> 23:07.821
THOSE ARE DEAD BODIES.

23:16.960 --> 23:19.180
HEY! RICK!
RICK PAGE.

23:19.223 --> 23:21.269
HEY, RICK. UH, DO YOU KNOW
WHAT'S HAPPENING RIGHT NOW?

23:21.312 --> 23:22.618
UH, LAST THING I REMEMBER,

23:22.662 --> 23:24.315
I WAS READING SALES FORECASTS
IN THE BACK.

23:24.359 --> 23:26.013
GEEZ,
THOSE THINGS ARE DULL.

23:26.056 --> 23:28.450
YOU EVER HEARD OF THE DANDY LION
CAR COMPANY?
NOPE.

23:28.494 --> 23:30.147
YOU WANT TO OPEN THE KIMONO

23:30.191 --> 23:32.498
ON WHY I'M WEARING
A SILVER LEOTARD AND
HANGING FROM A HOOK?

23:32.541 --> 23:35.414
DO YOU HAVE ANY LAST REQUESTS
OR THOUGHTS?

23:35.457 --> 23:38.417
IF I WANTED TO MINGLE WITH A
BUNCH OF GEEKS WEARING LEOTARDS,

23:38.460 --> 23:40.244
I'D HAVE STAYED
IN ART SCHOOL.

23:40.288 --> 23:41.550
YOU WENT TO ART SCHOOL?

23:41.594 --> 23:43.030
DIDN'T KNOW THAT, DID YOU?

23:44.901 --> 23:46.381
AAH!

23:46.425 --> 23:48.252
AAAAAAAH!

23:48.296 --> 23:49.340
STOP IT!

23:51.473 --> 23:53.997
I WAS JUST RIDING THE FERRIS
WHEEL AT THE STATE FAIR,

23:54.041 --> 23:57.479
AND THE TEENAGER RUNNING IT SAID
I COULD RIDE AN EXTRA...TURN.

23:57.523 --> 23:59.612
DID YOU EVER HEAR OF
THE DANDY LION CAR COMPANY?

23:59.655 --> 24:00.613
NO.

24:00.656 --> 24:01.962
MOVING ON.WAIT A SEC.

24:02.005 --> 24:03.442
I DID CHECK A BOX THAT SAID

24:03.485 --> 24:05.139
I COULD BE USED TO TEST
AUTOMOBILE SAFETY.

24:05.182 --> 24:07.358
SOUNDS SCARY, BUT WHEN
YOU'RE DEAD, YOU'RE DEAD.

24:07.402 --> 24:08.708
AM I DEAD?

24:11.275 --> 24:13.452
THERE'S NOTHING ILLEGAL
ABOUT ANY OF THAT?

24:13.495 --> 24:15.192
AND WHY WOULD
DANDY LION REPLACE

24:15.236 --> 24:17.238
ALL THEIR CRASH-TEST DUMMIES
WITH DEAD BODIES?

24:17.281 --> 24:19.762
AND WHAT HAPPENED TO ALL
THE REALDUMMIES?

24:19.806 --> 24:22.983
Narrator: BEFORE EMERSON COD
COULD REPLY WITH A CLEVER

24:23.026 --> 24:24.724
IF SLIGHTLY INSULTING REMARK...

24:24.767 --> 24:25.681
Shh, Shh.

24:26.856 --> 24:28.858
SEE THAT?

24:42.350 --> 24:44.483
JEANINE?

24:46.920 --> 24:49.009
[ MUMBLING ]

24:49.052 --> 24:50.445
WHAT?

24:54.580 --> 24:56.320
I COULDN'T TELL YOU
ANYTHING BEFORE

24:56.364 --> 24:58.018
BECAUSE THEY WERE
WATCHING ME.

24:58.061 --> 25:00.629
I HID AT WORK TO MAKE SURE
NO ONE WOULD FOLLOW ME HOME.

25:00.673 --> 25:03.197
THE TRUTH IS BERNIE AND I
WERE SO IN LOVE.

25:03.240 --> 25:05.721
IT ALL STARTED WHEN HE CAME TO
SEE THIS SALES TRAINING THING

25:05.765 --> 25:08.158
ON HIS LONG LUNCH BREAK,
AND IT WAS LOVE AT FIRST SIGHT.

25:08.202 --> 25:10.465
I COULDN'T TAKE MY EYES OFF HIM.
HE JUST MESMERIZED ME.

25:10.509 --> 25:13.512
MY HEART LEAPT OUT OF MY CHEST,
AND I JUST COULDN'T LOOK AWAY.

25:13.555 --> 25:16.123
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT WAS.
I GOT ALL MISTY-EYED, YOU KNOW?

25:16.166 --> 25:19.648
Narrator:
AND AS JEANINE CONTINUED TO EAT
HER TRIPLE-BERRY PIE,

25:19.692 --> 25:21.868
SHE TOLD THEM
THE STORY OF HER LOVE AFFAIR

25:21.911 --> 25:24.000
WITH BERNARD SLAYBECK.

25:24.044 --> 25:27.700
PRESENT, PRESENT, PRESENT,
PRESENT, PRESENT, PRESENT,

25:27.743 --> 25:30.572
AND GIGGLE, GIGGLE,
GIGGLE, GIGGLE, GOOD GIRLS.

25:30.616 --> 25:33.053
Narrator: THEY HAD MET
WHEN THE SCIENTIST HAD COME

25:33.096 --> 25:36.056
TO WATCH SALES TRAINING
ON A LONG LUNCH.

25:36.099 --> 25:38.275
THE ATTRACTION
WAS INSTANTANEOUS,

25:38.319 --> 25:41.452
AND THEY WOULD BOTH CONFESS TO
REPLAYING THIS FIRST ENCOUNTER

25:41.496 --> 25:44.673
AS THEY FELL ASLEEP
IN THEIR BEDS THAT NIGHT.

25:44.717 --> 25:49.983
HE WOULD REMEMBER HER HAIR
AS BEING SLIGHTLY REDDER,

25:50.026 --> 25:51.898
HER SWEATER SLIGHTLY TIGHTER,

25:51.941 --> 25:57.033
BUT THE SMILE HE WOULD GET
JUST RIGHT.

25:57.077 --> 26:00.297
SHE WOULD REMEMBER HIS LOOK
AS SHY BUT FLIRTATIOUS,

26:00.341 --> 26:02.125
HIS TIE AS RED BUT VERY THIN,

26:02.169 --> 26:04.737
AND THAT HIS SANDWICH
WAS AN ANGUS BEEF PATTY

26:04.780 --> 26:07.087
WITH BUTTERHEAD LETTUCE,
ROMA TOMATOES,

26:07.130 --> 26:09.132
ON A SESAME-SEED
WHOLE-WHEAT BUN,

26:09.176 --> 26:12.962
AND A GLASS OF 2% MILK.

26:13.006 --> 26:17.010
AS THEY TALKED, THESE ARE THE
THINGS SHE CAME TO KNOW FIRST.

26:17.053 --> 26:20.317
THE SCIENTIST WAS KIND.
THE SCIENTIST WAS LONELY.

26:20.361 --> 26:23.146
THE SCIENTIST CAME ALIVE
WHEN HE TOLD HER

26:23.190 --> 26:25.932
ABOUT HIS HOBBY
OF CATCHING BUTTERFLIES.

26:25.975 --> 26:29.152
WHEN HE ADMITTED THAT HE ALWAYS
SET THEM FREE,

26:29.196 --> 26:32.808
SHE FELT DIZZY
AND GIGGLED FOR NO REASON.

26:32.852 --> 26:34.505
[ GIGGLES ]

26:42.601 --> 26:46.126
Narrator:
THE WAIF AND THE SCIENTIST
FELL DEEPLY IN LOVE,

26:46.169 --> 26:50.173
HIDING THEIR AFFAIR FROM
THE WORLD LIKE A TRADE SECRET.

26:58.181 --> 27:02.882
BUT JEANINE FROM PROMOTIONS FELT
A CHASM GROWING BETWEEN THEM.

27:06.363 --> 27:08.757
AS THE LAUNCH OF THE FLOWER CAR
GREW CLOSER,

27:08.801 --> 27:10.846
BERNARD'S HOURS GREW LONGER.

27:18.375 --> 27:21.378
HE BECAME DISTANT
AND HARD TO REACH.

27:24.425 --> 27:28.124
SUSPECTING HER SAFETY SCIENTIST
OF STEPPING OUT ON HER,

27:28.168 --> 27:29.691
SHE BEGAN TO SPY.

27:29.735 --> 27:31.432
BUT THERE WAS NO OTHER FLOWER,

27:31.475 --> 27:34.696
ONLY MYSTERIOUS TRIPS
INTO THE DARKNESS.

27:42.443 --> 27:44.401
WHERE DID SHE GO?

27:44.445 --> 27:47.622
SORRY. RESTROOM.
MINT, ANYONE?

27:47.666 --> 27:49.058
NO, THANKS.

27:49.102 --> 27:50.712
WHERE WAS SLAYBECK GOING
ON THESE NIGHT DRIVES?

27:50.756 --> 27:52.018
I COULD NEVER SEE.

27:52.061 --> 27:53.323
AND WHEN I CONFRONTED HIM
ABOUT IT,

27:53.367 --> 27:54.934
HE WOULDN'T TELL ME
ANYTHING.

27:54.977 --> 27:57.240
I THOUGHT I WAS BEING PARANOID
TILL HE TURNED UP DEAD.

27:57.284 --> 27:59.286
YOU GONNA FINISH THAT?YES.

27:59.329 --> 28:01.201
I WISH WE KNEW
WHAT HE WAS DOING.

28:01.244 --> 28:03.420
OH, I FIGURED IT OUT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:05.596 --> 28:08.425
Narrator:
THE FLOWER WAS NO FOOL.

28:12.081 --> 28:15.650
HER INFORMATION WAS VALUABLE,
AND THE PRICE WAS PIE.

28:35.148 --> 28:37.237
IT'S EASIER IF I SHOW YOU.
FOLLOW ME.

28:37.280 --> 28:38.673
SHOTGUN!
CHUCK!

28:38.717 --> 28:39.892
I HATE THE BACK.

28:39.935 --> 28:42.721
DEAD, AGAIN, FOREVER.

28:42.764 --> 28:45.419
FINE.

28:45.462 --> 28:47.247
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:53.122 --> 28:54.471
Chuck:
SHE'S NOT GOING VERY FAST.

28:54.515 --> 28:56.256
Ned: THAT CAR CAN'T HAVE
A VERY BIG ENGINE.

28:56.299 --> 28:57.953
MAYBE SHE ATE IT.

28:57.997 --> 28:59.346
THAT'S NOT FUNNY.

28:59.389 --> 29:01.261
SHE OBVIOUSLY HAS
A VERY SERIOUS DISORDER.

29:01.304 --> 29:02.915
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?SERIOUSLY?

29:02.958 --> 29:05.439
THE GIRL'S GOT A WHOLE SECRET
LIFE IN THE BATHROOM.

29:05.482 --> 29:07.267
AND I KNOW EXACTLY
HOW SHE FEELS.

29:07.310 --> 29:08.659
SO DO I.

29:08.703 --> 29:10.487
I HATE HAVING SECRETS.
NOW I AM ONE --

29:10.531 --> 29:12.794
ALL THESE DISGUISES, HIDING
IN YOUR APARTMENT ALL THE TIME.

29:12.838 --> 29:14.753
I HATE SECRETS, TOO.YOU LOVESECRETS.

29:14.796 --> 29:16.276
YOU WANT TO MARRY SECRETS

29:16.319 --> 29:18.321
AND HAVE LITTLE HALF-SECRET,
HALF-HUMAN BABIES.

29:19.845 --> 29:21.977
WELL, I HAVE A SECRET, TOO.
I DO MISS MY AUNTS.

29:22.021 --> 29:24.023
IF I CAN'T HAVE THEM BACK,
THEN ALL I HAVE IS YOU.

29:24.066 --> 29:25.633
WHICH IS GREAT, BUT...

29:25.676 --> 29:27.809
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT YOU
SINCE YOU WERE 9.

29:27.853 --> 29:29.811
IT'S PRETTY MUCH I BAKE PIES
AND WAKE THE DEAD.

29:29.855 --> 29:31.247
I LIVE A VERY
SHELTERED LIFE.

29:31.291 --> 29:33.206
I ALREADY LIVED
A SHELTERED LIFE ONCE.

29:33.249 --> 29:35.425
BUT IT WASN'T AS SHELTERED
AS YOU THINK.

29:35.469 --> 29:38.602
AUNT LILY HAD A VERY EXTENSIVE
COLLECTION OF HISTORIC EROTICA

29:38.646 --> 29:39.952
HIDDEN IN THE MILK CELLAR.

29:39.995 --> 29:41.736
THE MILK CELLAR.

29:41.780 --> 29:43.782
THE CHEESE FLOOR, THE SPOOKY
PLACE UNDER THE HOUSE, WHATEVER.

29:43.825 --> 29:45.218
I WILL PAY BOTH OF YOU

29:45.261 --> 29:46.828
NOT TO HAVE THIS CONVERSATION
IN FRONT OF ME.

29:46.872 --> 29:49.483
IT'S NOT IN FRONT OF YOU.
IT'S TO THE SIDE AND BEHIND YOU.

29:49.526 --> 29:51.485
YOU CAN'T RIDE
IN THE FRONT, CHUCK.

29:51.528 --> 29:53.095
Narrator:
TRAGICALLY FOR JEANINE,

29:53.139 --> 29:55.097
IT DIDN'T MATTER WHERE SHESAT.

29:58.231 --> 29:59.972
[ TIRES SCREECHING ]

30:14.987 --> 30:17.337
THERE YOU GO.
GOOD AS NEW.

30:17.380 --> 30:18.555
DO I LOOK OKAY?

30:18.599 --> 30:20.644
RUNWAY READY.REALLY?

30:20.688 --> 30:22.603
YOU DON'T THINK THESE BANDAGES
MAKE ME LOOK FAT?

30:22.646 --> 30:23.865
NO, NOT AT ALL.

30:23.909 --> 30:27.477
THAT'S SO SWEET.
IS HE ALWAYS THIS SWEET?

30:27.521 --> 30:29.131
I WOULDN'T KNOW.

30:29.175 --> 30:31.220
LOOK, SOME CAR BOMBER JUST
WENT THROUGH A LOT OF TROUBLE

30:31.264 --> 30:33.135
TO KEEP YOU FROM
SHOWING US WHATEVER IT IS
YOU WANTED TO SHOW US.

30:33.179 --> 30:34.310
THE BODIES.

30:34.354 --> 30:35.790
WHAT BODIES?
THE DEAD BODIES?

30:35.834 --> 30:37.313
WE ALREADY FOUND
THE DEAD BODIES.

30:37.357 --> 30:40.708
NO. THE ONES
IN THE BIG HOLE.

30:50.936 --> 30:51.893
HOW SAD.

30:51.937 --> 30:54.069
WHY WOULD SOMEBODY
DO THIS?

30:54.113 --> 30:55.723
ONE WAY TO FIND OUT.

31:00.423 --> 31:02.425
WHAT IS ALL THAT?

31:02.469 --> 31:04.863
EACH ONE OF THESE
GUYS IS FITTED WITH
A COMPUTER HARD DRIVE

31:04.906 --> 31:06.777
TO RECORD ANY
OF THE CRASH-TEST DATA.

31:06.821 --> 31:08.867
YOU BURY THE DUMMIES,
YOU BURY THE DATA.

31:08.910 --> 31:10.172
COULDN'T THEY JUST
ERASE IT?

31:10.216 --> 31:12.218
YOU NEVER CAN COMPLETELY
ERASE ANYTHING.

31:12.261 --> 31:15.003
WHY ARE DEAD PEOPLE ON HOOKS
AND PLASTIC DUMMIES IN A GRAVE?

31:15.047 --> 31:17.005
THE COMPANY MUST HAVE
SWITCHED TO CADAVERS

31:17.049 --> 31:18.920
SO THAT THERE'D BE
NO PERMANENT RECORD

31:18.964 --> 31:20.356
OF THE CRASH-TEST
RESULTS,

31:20.400 --> 31:21.967
'CAUSE DEAD PEOPLE
DON'T TALK...

31:22.010 --> 31:23.577
USUALLY.

31:25.492 --> 31:27.407
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

31:34.327 --> 31:35.763
UGH.
UGH.

31:35.806 --> 31:36.546
[ GASPS ]

31:41.073 --> 31:43.205
Narrator: AS THE PIE MAKER'S
BRAIN CRACKLED

31:43.249 --> 31:47.383
WITH 10,000 VOLTS OF ELECTRICITY
AND THEN LOST CONSCIOUSNESS,

31:47.427 --> 31:49.211
OLIVE WOULD HAVE NO SUCH LUCK.

31:49.255 --> 31:51.213
DIGBY, YOU AWAKE?

31:51.257 --> 31:52.954
[ WHINES ]

31:52.998 --> 31:54.564
I CAN'T SLEEP, EITHER.

31:54.608 --> 31:56.915
Narrator: CLOSING HER EYES
ONLY MADE HER VISIONS

31:56.958 --> 31:58.699
OF THE PIE MAKER'S
LATE-NIGHT DATE

31:58.742 --> 32:00.701
WITH THE PERKY BRUNETTE
FROM NOWHERE

32:00.744 --> 32:03.095
MORE VIVID AND UNCENSORED.

32:09.362 --> 32:11.538
OH! YUCK.

32:11.581 --> 32:14.758
Narrator:
OLIVE DECIDED SHE WAS DONE
LYING DOWN ABOUT THIS.

32:14.802 --> 32:19.459
WE ARE UP.
WE ARE WALKING.

32:37.129 --> 32:38.260
[ Muffled ] LOOK.

32:38.304 --> 32:39.958
[ GASPS ]

32:45.354 --> 32:47.617
[ GLASS SCRAPING ]

32:47.661 --> 32:49.489
[ GROANING ]

32:56.322 --> 32:59.586
AUTOMOBILE MANUFACTURING
IS A DIRTY BUSINESS.

32:59.629 --> 33:02.458
Narrator: MURDER WAS NOT NEW
FOR MARK CHASE.

33:02.502 --> 33:05.374
LUCKILY, BODY BAGS KEEP THINGS
NICE AND NEAT.

33:06.723 --> 33:08.638
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE.

33:08.682 --> 33:11.206
THROUGH A SERIES
OF CRASH-TEST EXPERIMENTS,

33:11.250 --> 33:14.035
BERNARD SLAYBECK HAD LEARNED
THAT THE DANDY LION

33:14.079 --> 33:15.254
WAS A DEADLY DUD.

33:25.351 --> 33:29.094
BERNARD BEGGED THE PRESIDENT
TO CANCEL THE CAR'S LAUNCH,

33:29.137 --> 33:32.749
BUT MARK CHASE HAD OTHER PLANS.

33:36.231 --> 33:40.888
LIKE A SMOKING GUN, THE SMOKING
DUMMIES WOULD HAVE TO BE BURIED.

33:40.931 --> 33:44.022
THE COMPANY HAD INVESTED
MILLIONS IN THE DANDY LION,

33:44.065 --> 33:46.676
AND HE KNEW THAT KEEPING
THIS TERRIBLE SECRET

33:46.720 --> 33:50.115
WOULD STILL BE CHEAPER THAN
HALTING PRODUCTION OF THE CAR.

33:53.770 --> 33:57.078
A DECISION WAS MADE,
A COVER-UP UNDERTAKEN.

33:57.122 --> 33:58.906
IF THE DUMMIES HAD TO GO,

33:58.949 --> 34:01.865
SO WOULD ANY DUMMY
WHO GOT IN THE WAY.

34:20.493 --> 34:21.885
AS HE REGAINED CONSCIOUSNESS

34:21.929 --> 34:23.539
AND HURTLED
TOWARD THE CRASH-TEST WALL,

34:23.583 --> 34:25.976
BERNARD'S ONLY THOUGHTS
WERE OF JEANINE

34:26.020 --> 34:29.067
AND HOW HE WISHED
HE'D TOLD HER HE LOVED HER.

34:37.292 --> 34:41.079
MARK CHASE'S ATTENTION TO DETAIL
AND GIFT FOR PLANNING

34:41.122 --> 34:45.170
HAD SERVED HIM WELL AS A C.E.O.,
AND NOW AGAIN AS A MURDERER.

34:45.213 --> 34:46.780
HIS COVER-UP COMPLETE,

34:46.823 --> 34:49.522
HIS ONLY THOUGHTS WERE
THAT THE DANDY LION SX

34:49.565 --> 34:53.395
WOULDBLOOM ON TIME
AND NO ONE WOULD STOP HIM.

34:57.791 --> 35:00.533
THE DANDY LION CAR IS THE
CULMINATION OF MY LIFE'S WORK.

35:00.576 --> 35:02.012
IT IS
A FLOWER-POWERED PHENOMENON

35:02.056 --> 35:03.623
BORNE OF A THOUSAND
SLEEPLESS NIGHTS,

35:03.666 --> 35:05.059
INTENSE RITALIN ABUSE,

35:05.103 --> 35:06.582
AND A LONG-SUBLIMATED INTEREST
IN BOTANY.

35:06.626 --> 35:09.672
SO WHAT IF IN THE UNLIKELY
BUT NOT IMPOSSIBLE EVENT

35:09.716 --> 35:11.848
THAT THE CAR GETS UP TO A SPEED
OF 70 MILES AN HOUR,

35:11.892 --> 35:14.024
WITH THE HEADLIGHTS ON
AND THE SEAT WARMER ON LOW,

35:14.068 --> 35:15.287
A SHORT-CIRCUIT IN THE RADIO

35:15.330 --> 35:16.853
CAUSES A CATACLYSMIC
CHAIN REACTION

35:16.897 --> 35:18.768
THAT BLOWS THE CAR
AND ITS PRECIOUS HUMAN CARGO

35:18.812 --> 35:20.161
TO SMITHEREENS?!

35:20.205 --> 35:22.598
Narrator: AS MARK CHASE
CONTINUED HIS MONOLOGUE,

35:22.642 --> 35:25.253
UNAWARE THAT IT WAS
COMPLETELY INAUDIBLE

35:25.297 --> 35:28.300
FROM WITHIN THE SEALED BODY BAGS
WITHIN THE CAR,

35:28.343 --> 35:32.173
CHUCK PONDERED WHY IT WAS
SHE ALWAYS SEEMED TO DIE

35:32.217 --> 35:35.437
JUST AS THINGS WERE STARTING
TO GET GOOD.

35:35.481 --> 35:37.700
SON OF A BITCH.

35:37.744 --> 35:39.006
WHAT?

35:39.049 --> 35:40.486
Narrator:
AND THOUGH HE COULDN'T HEAR HER,

35:40.529 --> 35:43.010
NED SUDDENLY WANTED
TO TELL HER EVERYTHING --

35:43.053 --> 35:45.404
PET PEEVES AND FAVORITE FOODS,

35:45.447 --> 35:47.362
HIS FEARS, HIS DREAMS,

35:47.406 --> 35:51.671
AND ALL THE PURE JOY
SHE HAD BROUGHT INTO HIS LIFE.

35:51.714 --> 35:54.804
SAYONARA.

35:54.848 --> 35:58.547
Narrator: THIS WAS THE END
ALL OVER AGAIN.

35:58.591 --> 36:01.028
GOODBYE.

36:25.095 --> 36:27.533
Narrator: EMERSON COD DID NOT
LIKE TO KNIT IN PUBLIC,

36:27.576 --> 36:30.449
BUT HE OFTEN LEFT THE HOUSE
WITH THE NEEDLES IN HIS POCKET,

36:30.492 --> 36:33.365
SHOULD THE OPPORTUNITY
TO RIB-STITCH A SKI CAP

36:33.408 --> 36:35.193
PRESENT ITSELF.

36:42.200 --> 36:43.201
DRIVE!
OOH!

37:06.136 --> 37:08.748
Narrator: IF ONLY THE PIE MAKER
HAD HEARD THE KILLER EXPLAIN

37:08.791 --> 37:12.273
THAT THE DANDY LION SX WAS MUCH
MORE THAN AN ECO-FRIENDLY CAR

37:12.317 --> 37:13.666
OF THE FUTURE.

37:13.709 --> 37:16.364
IF ONLY HE'D HEARD
IT WAS ALSO A DEATHTRAP,

37:16.408 --> 37:19.324
A DANDELION-FUELED TIME BOMB.

37:30.857 --> 37:33.990
COME ON.
JUST A LITTLE FASTER.

37:35.427 --> 37:37.342
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:38.995 --> 37:40.301
[ TIRES SCREECHING ]

37:40.345 --> 37:41.259
AAH!AAH!

37:43.783 --> 37:45.567
CAN'T THIS CAR GO ANY FASTER?!

37:45.611 --> 37:47.265
SOME CAR OF THE FUTURE
THIS IS!

37:47.308 --> 37:49.267
I THOUGHT THE CAR OF THE FUTURE
WAS SUPPOSED TO FLY.

37:49.310 --> 37:51.007
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED
TO FLYING CARS?

37:52.357 --> 37:53.358
OH.
AAH!

37:55.185 --> 37:55.969
OHH!

37:56.012 --> 37:57.362
WHOA!
WHOA!

37:57.405 --> 37:58.624
WHOA!
WHOA!

37:58.667 --> 37:59.886
WHOA!
WHOA!

37:59.929 --> 38:06.066
WHOOOOA!WHOOOOA!WHOOOOA!

38:15.118 --> 38:16.772
[ SIREN WAILING ]

38:19.079 --> 38:21.255
Narrator: IN THE UNLIKELY
BUT NOT IMPOSSIBLE EVENT

38:21.299 --> 38:23.910
OF REACHING THE SPEED
OF 70 MILES AN HOUR

38:23.953 --> 38:26.956
WITH THE HEADLIGHTS ON
AND THE SEAT WARMER SET TO LOW,

38:27.000 --> 38:28.654
A SHORT-CIRCUIT IN THE RADIO

38:28.697 --> 38:31.352
WOULD SET OFF A CATACLYSMIC
CHAIN REACTION

38:31.396 --> 38:34.486
THAT WOULD BLOW THE CAR
AND ITS PRECIOUS HUMAN CARGO

38:34.529 --> 38:36.270
TO SMITHEREENS.

38:36.314 --> 38:38.968
JEANINE HAD BEEN THE FIRST
UNFORTUNATE VICTIM, AND NOW...

38:39.012 --> 38:41.319
WATCH OUT!

38:41.362 --> 38:44.713
AAAAAH!
AAAAAH!AAAAAH!

38:44.757 --> 38:47.020
AAAAAH!AAAAAH!AAAAAH!AAAAAH!

38:51.372 --> 38:55.463
Narrator:
THE PIE MAKER HAD NEVER BEEN
SO HAPPY TO SEE OLIVE.

38:55.507 --> 38:59.424
OLIVE HAD NEVER BEEN SO HAPPY
TO SEE THE PIE MAKER.

38:59.467 --> 39:00.555
YOU OKAY?

39:00.599 --> 39:03.689
I AM NOW.

39:03.732 --> 39:06.169
WHATEVER THE PIE MAKER
HAD BEEN DOING THAT NIGHT

39:06.213 --> 39:08.998
DID NOT SEEM
ESPECIALLY ROMANTIC.

39:09.042 --> 39:11.392
CAN YOU HELP US GET OUT
OF THESE BODY BAGS?

39:11.436 --> 39:13.394
SURE.

39:13.438 --> 39:15.178
[ INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER ]

39:15.222 --> 39:17.920
Narrator: MARK CHASE'S CHASE
HAD COME TO AN END.

39:17.964 --> 39:20.836
HIS PLAN FOILED AND
THE POLICE NOW CLOSING IN,

39:20.880 --> 39:22.577
THE CAR MAKER TRIED TO FLEE,

39:22.621 --> 39:25.667
ONLY TO DISCOVER
HE WAS OUT OF GAS.

39:25.711 --> 39:28.104
UNLIKE THE PIE MAKER
AND HIS FRIENDS,

39:28.148 --> 39:30.803
THE DANDY LION CAR COMPANY
DID NOT SURVIVE

39:30.846 --> 39:33.196
ONCE ITS DARK SECRETS
WERE REVEALED.

39:33.240 --> 39:39.072
THOSE RESPONSIBLE WERE PUNISHED
FOR THEIR WICKED WAYS.

39:45.078 --> 39:46.862
OTHERS, STRENGTHENED BY THE NEWS

39:46.906 --> 39:49.430
THAT THEIR LOVED ONES
HAD NOT DIED IN VAIN,

39:49.474 --> 39:50.866
REACHED OUT FOR THE HELP

39:50.910 --> 39:52.520
AND ROUND-THE-CLOCK
SURVEILLANCE

39:52.564 --> 39:55.567
BY A NUTRITION PROFESSIONAL
THAT THEY NEEDED.

40:00.528 --> 40:02.400
AND EMERSON COD REALIZED

40:02.443 --> 40:05.664
HE WOULD NOT BE NOT KNITTING
ANYTIME SOON,

40:05.707 --> 40:08.536
AS THE DEAD GIRL,
WHO WAS NOT DEAD,

40:08.580 --> 40:11.017
APPEARED TO BE STAYING PUT...

40:12.453 --> 40:14.542
SWEET.

40:14.586 --> 40:18.241
...A FACT
THE PIE MAKER CELEBRATED.

40:19.765 --> 40:21.244
[ DOOR OPENS, BELLS RING ]

40:21.288 --> 40:22.855
NOT GIVING UP, DIGBY.

40:22.898 --> 40:24.160
Ned: GET IN.

40:24.204 --> 40:26.685
THE FRONT?

40:26.728 --> 40:28.469
[ KNOCKS ]YOU DID THIS?

40:28.513 --> 40:30.253
YOU CAN DRIVE NOW, TOO,
IF YOU WANT...

40:30.297 --> 40:32.081
BUT I KIND OF LOVE DRIVING.

40:32.125 --> 40:33.735
REALLY?
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT ABOUT YOU.

40:35.302 --> 40:36.956
WHAT IS THAT?

40:36.999 --> 40:39.872
IT'S FOR, UM...

40:39.915 --> 40:41.656
STEERING EMERGENCIES.

40:41.700 --> 40:42.744
Narrator: HE LIED.

40:42.788 --> 40:45.094
PERFECT.

40:46.487 --> 40:48.054
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

40:48.097 --> 40:49.751
Narrator:
SHE LIED, TOO.
